title: Massive search operation for cop killer Dezi Freeman | 7NEWS
description: A major five-day police operation involving over 100 officers and volunteers is underway in Victoria's Mount Buffalo National Park area, searching for fugitive Dezi Freeman, who killed two police officers and wounded another five months ago. The search, based on intelligence about a gunshot heard an hour after the original fatal shooting, includes specialist search and rescue teams, a drone unit and a cadaver dog. Separately, emergency crews are resuming the search for a missing male swimmer in his 30s at South Maroubra Beach in Sydney, where difficult weather conditions are hampering rescue efforts. title: 'Particularly terrifying': Novotel staff threatened in early morning hotel robbery | 7NEWS
description: Two masked men threatened and detained hotel staff during an armed robbery at a Haymarket hotel on Little Pier Street at approximately 5:40am. The offenders, one armed with a screwdriver, stole a portable safe containing documents before fleeing in a stolen beige Volvo.   Police are releasing CCTV footage and seeking public assistance to identify the suspects. title: 'The largest manhunt that we have seen in Victoria': Hunt for cop killer continues | 7NEWS
description: Police are conducting a new five-day search operation for Dezi Freeman, the fugitive wanted for killing two police officers and seriously injuring a third on 26 August. The manhunt, described as the largest in Victoria and the largest tactical operation in Australia, has entered its sixth month with Freeman remaining at large.   Police are exploring three scenarios: that Freeman is dead in the Mount Buffalo area, being harboured by others, or on the run unassisted.   A $1 million reward is offered for information leading to his arrest or location. title: Second victim comes out alleging former royal of sexual encounters
description: A second woman has come forward alleging sex offender Jeffery Epstein sent her to the UK for a sexual encounter with the-now King's brother, Andrew Mountbatten-Windsor. This follows new Epstein documents released by the US Justice Department which revealed images of Andrew on all fours on top of an unidentified woman. #documents #files #royals #worldnews  If you or someone you know is impacted by sexual assault, domestic or family violence, call 1800 737 732 or visit 1800RESPECT.org.au.
